text: Hi <@U014A8JD9DH> @*<https://app.slack.com/team/UFBNA9K9A|Zack Wolfson> ,* Is there any API/way to fetch Objects list.
And any API by which we can Test Connecion( test {{hapikey}} is valid or not).
Hi all, does anyone know how to fetch list of Objects available in HubSpot for a specific hapikey?
And Is there any API by which we can Test Connecion( test {{hapikey}} is valid or not).

Not at all. And I've tried multiple ways to pull it in. Adobe generates a custom css file with whichever fonts I choose. So I tried that method of calling in that CSS file in the <head>, then using a font-family declaration for items using that font. But this method does not work. That font-family declaration I've tried using multiple methods (using single quotes, double quotes, what Adobe says to use, what a HubSpot reference said to use, etc) to no avail. I have not tried just downloading the fonts and uploading into HS yet.
And thank you so much for helping me with this, I greatly appreciate it.

<@UFAANRW07> Ive never had an issue with adobe typekits before when using them with HubSpot - Is there a preview page you could send over? DM me if you would prefer.

Adding this to the head should be just fine. Then declare using font-family in css

```<link rel="stylesheet" href="<https://use.typekit.net/(yourTypeKit).css>">```
